data.description: Discover rural living in Tecumseh, Oklahoma—a four-bedroom haven on 2.3 acres. Nestled at the crossroads of two main roads, the property offers not just a home but potential for added structures, thanks to extensive road frontage for a potential back-of-property shop. Privacy prevails with a secluded driveway, hidden by overgrowth, shielding the residence and offering tranquility. The front porch beckons with views, particularly enchanting in autumn, creating an ideal spot for relaxation.Inside, over 2400 sq ft unfolds with two spacious living rooms, a formal dining room, and a well-equipped kitchen. The primary suite impresses with a king-size bed, workout station, and a full bath boasting a garden tub and walk-in shower. The kitchen, a focal point, boasts abundant cabinetry, a cozy coffee nook, and a designated area for fruit baskets. The dining room, spacious and with patio access, enhances the indoor-outdoor living experience. Beyond, practical amenities include a storm shelter, ensuring resident peace of mind. Outdoor spaces—a picnic nook and reading area—add charm. For the green thumb or homesteader, the land offers a goat/calf/lamb pen and a top-notch chicken coop, think of the daily egg bounty. This Tecumseh property seamlessly blends comfort with rural living's joys, appealing to those seeking affordability, privacy, and a connection to nature.
